## 6 · How to apply this

### 6.1 In a STYLE_DECON.md

Each archetype guide's "Brand Adaptation" section should reference this file rather than inlining values:

> See `style-guides/BRAND.md`. The format and grammar of [archetype] applies as documented; all colors, type voices, and speaker grading defer to BRAND.md unless a specific override is noted below.

### 6.2 In a video composition

Drop these CSS variables into a shared `assets/brand-tokens.css` and `@import` it in every composition's root:

```css
:root {
  --primary-mid:        #XXXXXX;
  --primary-deep:       #XXXXXX;
  --primary-light:      #XXXXXX;
  --anchor-near-black:  #XXXXXX;
  --background-paper:   #XXXXXX;
  --accent-warm:        #XXXXXX;
  --accent-alert:       #XXXXXX;
}
```

### 6.3 When this file changes

A change here cascades to every archetype guide and every video composition. Treat updates with care. Any color or type-voice change should be discussed before committing - it changes the visual identity of every future video.

